  "narrative": {
    "intro": "NAICS 561110 obligations totaled $293M in FY2026 to date, with 813 awards and an average award size of $361K. Obligations fell 55.5% year over year. FY2026 to date spending sits well below recent full-year totals: FY21 totaled $766M, FY22 totaled $915M, FY23 totaled $850M, FY24 totaled $789M, and FY25 totaled $659M. The Department of Defense is the largest buyer in FY2026 to date with $151M in obligations, followed by the Department of Homeland Security with $40M and the National Aeronautics and Space Administration with $30.4M. Other significant buyers include the Department of Health and Human Services with $18.1M and the Department of Energy with $11.5M. Among vendors, KONIAG BRILLIENT, LLC and BOWHEAD MARINE SUPPORT SERVICES, LLC lead the list with $22.8M and $22.7M respectively, followed by SCIOLEX CORPORATION with $17.8M. Current-year totals are partial (fiscal year to date) and reflect early-year contracting activity rather than a full fiscal cycle.",
    "sections": [
      {
        "heading": "How has NAICS 561110 federal spending trended recently?",
        "body": "Obligations fell 55.5% year over year, with FY2026 to date obligations at $293M compared with prior full-year totals of $659M in FY25 and $789M in FY24. The five-year sequence shows FY21 $766M, FY22 $915M, FY23 $850M, FY24 $789M, and FY25 $659M, indicating FY2026 to date is materially lower than recent years. Current-year totals are partial (fiscal year to date) and may not represent a full fiscal cycle."
      },
      {
        "heading": "Which agencies and vendors dominate FY2026 to date obligations?",
        "body": "The Department of Defense accounts for the largest share with $151M in FY2026 to date obligations, followed by the Department of Homeland Security with $40M and the National Aeronautics and Space Administration with $30.4M. Top vendors by obligations in FY2026 to date are KONIAG BRILLIENT, LLC ($22.8M), BOWHEAD MARINE SUPPORT SERVICES, LLC ($22.7M), and SCIOLEX CORPORATION ($17.8M)."
      }
    ]
